<br>
Their jobs depend on the success of this game. That's a huge motivation to do it right. Take a look at some of the recent Devs' posts and you will see that they honestly want this game to continue to succeed. That recent guild summit was a good example of some new ways of thinking that will help to improve the game. <br>
<br>
I know many people are getting burned out, even I have lost some motivation, but these recent events and announcements have made me much more optimistic for the future. <br>
<br>
That said, epic 2.0s are so going to rule. The game needs something, a lot of somethings, to add that old spark back into it. And because they want our money for 4 more years, they are going to do it right. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=772824"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~toccard/Yuma.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
